      How often should I change my engine air filter?
      every 12,000 to 15,000 miles
      Replacement Time

      Check your owner's manual; it should tell you when your air filter should be replaced. This is generally every 12,000 to 15,000 miles, depending on your vehicle. If you have driven more than that since the last time you replaced the air filter, it's probably time to get it changed.      Oct 20, 2016
